ohha.puzzlecrafter.grid

Class CellCoordinate

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohha.puzzlecrafter.grid.CellCoordinate

  • public class CellCoordinate
extends Object
    Represents coordinates of a cell in the puzzle grid. They serve as conceptual wrappers for a pair of numbers. In particular, this means that they do not hold the actual values found in the puzzle's cells, see Grid for this.

    CellCoordinate objects are immutable, and the "modifier" methods return new CellCoordinate objects instead of modifying the CellCoordinate they were called on.

      • shiftX

        public CellCoordinate shiftX(int shift)
        Returns a new CellCoordinate with a shifted x-component. Specifically, the new CellCoordinate shares its y-component with the CellCoordinate the method was called on, and the new CellCoordinate's x-component is calculated by adding shift to the x-coordinate of the cell the method was called on.
        Parameters:
        shift - shift in the x-direction
        Returns:
        a new CellCoordinate with a shifted x-component

      • shiftY

        public CellCoordinate shiftY(int shift)
        Returns a new CellCoordinate with a shifted y-component. Specifically, the new CellCoordinate shares its x-component with the CellCoordinate the method was called on, and the new CellCoordinate's y-component is calculated by adding shift to the y-component of the cell the method was called on.
        Parameters:
        shift - shift in the y-direction
        Returns:
        a new CellCoordinate with a shifted y-component

      • switchX

        public CellCoordinate switchX(int newx)
        Returns a new CellCoordinate with the specified x-component. Specifically, the new CellCoordinate shares its y-component with the CellCoordinate the method was called on, and the new CellCoordinate's x-component is newx.
        Parameters:
        newx - the new x-coordinate
        Returns:
        a new CellCoordinate with a switched x-component

      • switchY

        Parameters:

        Returns:
        a new CellCoordinate with a switched y-component

      • getNeighbour

        public CellCoordinate getNeighbour(Side side)
        Returns a new CellCoordinate one step away from the given CellCoordinate in the given direction. As this method is grid-agnostic, it lets you step outside of the grid. For a method that doesn't return coordinates outside the given Grid, see Neighbours.
        Parameters:
        side - the direction of the wanted neighbour
        Returns:
        the coordinate of the neighbour

        Returns:
